<title>UK: British Gas Q2 in line with forecasts.</title>
<headline>British Gas Q2 in line with forecasts.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-09-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>Second quarter 1996</p>
<p>			   (million stg unless stated)</p>
<p> Historic cost net	8.0 loss	     vs 30 profit</p>
<p> Replacement cost net   127 loss	     vs 76 loss</p>
<p>					- Half year to June 30</p>
<p> Historic cost net	565 profit	   vs 635 profit</p>
<p> Replacement cost net   344 profit	   vs 429 profit</p>
<p>NOTE - Analysts' forecasts on second-quarter net historic cost results ranged from a 30 million stg loss to a 40 million stg profit.  </p>
<p>(All figures in million stg and second quarter except where stated)</p>
<p>HISTORICAL COST</p>
<p> Shr (pence)		0.2 loss	     vs 0.7 profit</p>
<p> H2 Dividend (pence)    6.4		    vs 6.4</p>
<p> Pretax		     7.0 loss	     vs 49.0 profit</p>
<p> Turnover		   1,886		  vs 1,657</p>
<p> Operating result	 40 profit	    vs 26 profit</p>
<p>CURRENT COST</p>
<p> Net taxed		  127 loss	     vs 76 loss</p>
<p> Basic share (pence)    2.9 loss	     vs 1.7 loss</p>
<p> Operating result	 101 loss	     vs 97 loss</p>
<p> Pretax		     126 loss	     vs 57 loss</p>
<p> Interest (payable)     64.0		   vs 10 (receivable)</p>
<p>	 NOTE - British Gas said it is &quot;making a final attempt&quot;</p>
<p>with regulator Ofgas to achieve a &quot;workable solution&quot; to the dispute over Ofgas's price control proposals for transmission operation Transco.</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7717</p>
